The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Rs 1000 cr for roads

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Nov. 13: The government today announced Rs 1,000 crore for road repairs across the state. 

 Only agencies that give a five-year guarantee on the repairs would be picked for the work, finance minister Asim Dasgupta said. Well reserve 15 per cent of the agencys repair funds for maintenance. If the condition of the road deteriorates within five years, we will deduct the amount from this reserve, he added.

 Zilla parishad chiefs and PWD officials have been asked to give a list of roads to be repaired. An official said the process of short-listing them will be over in 10 days. 

 Nuke power recce

 A Nuclear Power Corporation team will be here on Friday to evaluate the two possible sites along the East Midnapore coast for the proposed nuclear power station.

 Corporation chairman S.K. Jain will head the team. 

 We were given detailed parameters for the required site. The team will go through the data we have collected, a power department official said.




